# 28 Built-in Accessibility Features
## Assistive Technology Exception
Software that is assistive technology and supports the accessibility services of a platform is <stong>NOT required</strong> to conform to: 
* Chapter 5 requirements: https://www.access-board.gov/guidelines-and-standards/communications-and-it/about-the-section-508-standards/background/regulatory-assessment/chapter-5-estimated-benefits-of-standards
* E207.2: Requirement for platformsand applications to conform to Level A and Level AA Success Criteria
